HEADWORD: Ramie
<hw>Ram"ie</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧m"⟦esl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
Malay.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The grasscloth plant
(<spn>B⟦oe⟧hmeria nivea</spn>); also, its fiber, which is very fine and
exceedingly strong; -- called also <altname>China grass</altname>, and
<altname>rhea</altname>. See <cref>Grass-cloth plant</cref>, under
<er>Grass</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

